Commentary Text: Hardik Pandya to Boult, 1 run, MI have done it. They register their 100th win in T20s. The first team in the world to do so. At a venue against a strong KKR by resting 6 players. And they have ended KKR's unbeaten home chasing record here as well - that dated back to 2012. They were the last team to beat KKR here while defending and do it again now. Coming to how the last ball panned out - a mistimed slap to mid-off and that's game over. Contrasting emotions from both captains - Rohit is happy while Gambhir's face becomes even more grim.
